abstract: Elizabeth Warren was called out by rivals for a change, Joe Biden failed to stand out and Bernie Sanders calmed concerns about his health. Pete Buttigieg had his biggest night yet.
snippet: Elizabeth Warren was called out by rivals for a change, Joe Biden failed to stand out and Bernie Sanders calmed concerns about his health. Pete Buttigieg had his biggest night yet.
lead_paragraph: WESTERVILLE, Ohio — The CNN/New York Times debate on Tuesday night revealed new dynamics in the Democratic presidential race: Senator Elizabeth Warren took sustained fire from multiple rivals, former Vice President Joseph R. Biden Jr. struggled to make an impact and Mayor Pete Buttigieg and other candidates were newly aggressive in making their points.

headline_main: 6 Takeaways From the October Democratic Debate
byline_original: By Shane Goldmacher and Reid J. Epstein

abstract: After decades of trying to prove their toughness on national security, the candidates described an allies-first, tough-on-Russia foreign policy. But many of them, too, want to withdraw from the Middle East.
snippet: After decades of trying to prove their toughness on national security, the candidates described an allies-first, tough-on-Russia foreign policy. But many of them, too, want to withdraw from the Middle East.
lead_paragraph: WASHINGTON — For nearly two decades, Republicans have dominated national security debates, portraying themselves as tough on terrorists after the Sept. 11, 2001, attacks and tough on a recalcitrant, disruptive Russia. On Tuesday night, Democrats sensed an opportunity to retake that ground, attacking President Trump’s impulsive action in Syria as a gift to the Islamic State and to President Vladimir V. Putin of Russia.

abstract: Twelve Democratic presidential candidates shared the stage in Ohio for the fourth televised primary debate.
snippet: Twelve Democratic presidential candidates shared the stage in Ohio for the fourth televised primary debate.
lead_paragraph: Former Vice President Joseph R. Biden Jr. and Senator Elizabeth Warren got into a direct confrontation late in the debate on Tuesday night as the pair of Democratic front-runners compared their achievements in office and traded barbs.

abstract: “I believe Bernie Sanders is the best candidate to take on Donald Trump in 2020,” Ms. Omar said. Ms. Ocasio-Cortez will appear with Mr. Sanders at a rally on Saturday.
snippet: “I believe Bernie Sanders is the best candidate to take on Donald Trump in 2020,” Ms. Omar said. Ms. Ocasio-Cortez will appear with Mr. Sanders at a rally on Saturday.
lead_paragraph: WESTERVILLE, Ohio — Representative Ilhan Omar endorsed Senator Bernie Sanders of Vermont for the Democratic presidential nomination on Tuesday, and Representative Alexandria Ocasio-Cortez will endorse Mr. Sanders at a rally this weekend, according to his campaign.

abstract: Twelve Democratic presidential candidates shared the stage in Ohio for the fourth televised primary debate.
snippet: Twelve Democratic presidential candidates shared the stage in Ohio for the fourth televised primary debate.
lead_paragraph: Senator Kamala Harris of California pressed Senator Elizabeth Warren of Massachusetts about why she had not called on Twitter to suspend President Trump’s account during the Democratic presidential debate in Ohio on Tuesday.
headline_main: Warren and Harris Spar Over Trump’s Twitter Account

abstract: Mr. Sanders, 78, is trying to reassure voters of his stamina after he had a heart attack two weeks ago. Ms. Warren is in her 70s as well.
snippet: Mr. Sanders, 78, is trying to reassure voters of his stamina after he had a heart attack two weeks ago. Ms. Warren is in her 70s as well.
lead_paragraph: Loath as the candidates have been to talk about it, age is an inescapable subject in this Democratic primary: The three highest-polling candidates are all in their 70s, and one of them just had a heart attack.
headline_main: Bernie Sanders, Joe Biden and Elizabeth Warren Discuss Age at Debate
